reviews.content:
The first 20 minutes of this film are some of the best in the franchise. Jason is scary, the lighting is cool, and the killings are violent and sudden. Then, the film fast forwards 450 years and becomes a science fiction movie. But, not just any ol' sci-fi, but a specific type of sci-fi...In the 2000's, the Sci-Fi channel ran bad movies all weekend - movies they produced themselves, with bad acting, bad lighting, and bad special effects. No one complained, because it was just one channel wasting money on bad projects. 'Jason X' (2001) is a poorly produced Sci-Fi channel movie, made with Sci-Fi channel actors, in the same Canadian studios that produced all of the bad Sci-Fi channel movies that plagued the basic cable boxes of the early 2000's.With that said, there are some high points. Jason is scary and Lisa Ryder is hot as a robot. My favorite aspect of this film is the fact that, upon completion of this review, there is only one more in the franchise for me to watch. These are just historically bad movies.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
